At 05:00 PM 5/7/06, you wrote:
>the torque for the fill bolt on a 79 tranny or a 68 transaxle for a beetle...
>   i dont know if they would be the same and if 18ft pounds would be enough?
>

That is a tapered thread. I think 18fp is TOO MUCH. 10-12 is plenty. 
Just firm a firm hand on a short throw, not tight is right. I always 
use a short handled hex key or a shorty ratchet or a shorty wrench 
which is plenty tight not to back out.
